 						<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=9889"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			 			<A href="reply.php?board=player&id=9889"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A> </FONT>
			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			Since coming back to Archspace I have noticed several of the changes have not helped but hurt the game play and competitiveness.<br />
<br />
1 - Destroy Planets.  As much as we all like this ability, it is getting abused and makes it way too easy for someone to stay low and attack those who may be starting out or recently lost there fleets.<br />
<br />
Suggestions - I'm for removing this altogether, but at least something like only being able to destroy one planet at a time to prevent people from taking planets they don't want just to hurt someone else.<br />
<br />
2 - Attack Range.  The attack down range of 50% from 20% makes it too easy to hit someone with significantly smaller fleet.<br />
<br />
Suggestion - Return the attack range to where it was... it is too wide and again hurts the game play.<br />
<br />
3 - Attack Delay.  The delay preventing someone from attacking multiple times within the same turn or being attack multiple times was a good thing.  This just feeds planet grabbing and killing players off.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
I don't want you to think I hate the game or feel nothing positive has been done, so...<br />
<br />
Positive - The planet invest tool was a great tool and not only cuts down on tedious tasks, but allows more flexibility in planet investment and development.<br />
<br />
In general the level of cheating and server crashes has been greatly curbed and seems much more managible.<br />
<br />
Thanks to all and hope to see Archspace to continue to grow and improve.<br />
<br />
--CertGeek--						<P align=right> </P>
					</TD>
				</TR>
	
		
