				posted 2004-09-14 08:24&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=9894"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=9889"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	1. Destroy Planets - If your complaint is that the top players are blowing up planets, there are quicker ways to reduce your planet power.  Simply have a friend in your council declare war on you and take all of your planets (except a few).  When you are done, you could take them back, or better yet, have the top ranked player in your council take them all and become a permanent planet repository so that the top player can continually lend fleets to everyone else in the council.<br />
<br />
2. Attack Range - From what I have been able to discern, it would appear that honor is being implemented to curb attacks on weaker players.  At one point this set, whole fleets of dooms were running from single fleets of inneffective ships just because the player with dooms had an honor of 0.  Pretty cool, but I believe it will be toned down a little in the next set and it has been completely removed this set.  I do however agree with you in principle that something has to be done about being able to attack players half your size without even receiving a scratch.  If a tighter attack range is put in place it should be 80 - 125 or some other range that is fair for both attacker and defender and not the lopsided range that was in place in the old days.  I am willing to wait and see how the honor system plays out though, before I rant about tighter attack ranges again.<br />
<br />
3. Attack Delay - I assume you are suggesting a 10 minute delay.  That would mean that you could lose 6 planets an hour or 48 planets in the 8 hours that many people sleep.  So you can still be killed once you log off.  If you happen to be online when you are being wiped out you can place your fleets on the defensive and lose them, or if you have too many in your ship pool and not enough commanders, you can destroy them and drop out of range of your attackers.  If you are up against someone that is really out to kill you, there isn't much you can do about it even with a 10 minute limitation.  With the ten minute limitation, you wind up with combat that resembles the Black Market, where a group of players attacking a single target all just keep sending in their fleets as quickly as possible in hopes of being the lucky player to do the attack.  Is that really what you want?  Then it would become necessary to post the time that the player can be attacked again (and still everyone would then attack at that time and only one would get the prize and then everyone waits 10 more minutes for an opportunity to attack).<br />
<br />
Akira - My honor is at 96 and bad events still happen to me too, unless Mass Hysteria has suddenly been changed to a good event (I'm currently suffering that one right now).			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
