			  	I say the game, as it is, is really good! the attack ranges is well balanced, seeing as you lose honor for attacking someone really low below your power, as previously noted.<br />
<br />
The destroy planet function is there for a good reason. You can destroy multiple planets (after 95 turns or so) to get rid of the crap planets, reform your inner core, then remaking your outer core. It is also a risky gamble, seeing as if you are in a war, you can set possible planetary targets to be destroyed after 95 turns. If the planet gets taken, the person who recieved the planet would lose it instead of getting stronger by keeping a potentially useful planet.<br />
<br />
The only thing that i would say isn't very useful (at the moment due to possible server crash bugs unless it got fixed/taken out) is the auto-reply tool.<br />
<br />
<br />
BTW... this topic really should be under suggestions if you think about it ;)			   <P align=right></P>
