			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Thanks for the replies and feedback.  I posted this under suggestions as well.. but no one really adds much there.  Here atleast i can get some feed back and see what others are thinking.<br />
<br />
Nova - the fact that you can have a friend grab planets off you to reduce your value or take poor planets is not the same Destorying planets.  Now someone else is just carrying these planets and if a planet is deep enough into your core you'll have to pull other planets to get to it or just leave it.  I don't mind these tatics because the impact to the game play and competitiveness is minimal.<br />
<br />
But the ability to Destory planets adds a twist to the game play that unbalances it.  My suggest to limit it 1 planet at a time allows you to remove poor planets you not longer need for research or grabbed when exploring.<br />
<br />
<br />
The attack range hurts the most the game play... when someone twice your size decides to attack you there is not much you can do about it accept rebuilt.  The penalties associated with honor is not signicant to discourage these actions.<br />
<br />
Either increase the positives and negatives or honor or returning the attack range to only 20% smaller targets.			   <P align=right></P>
