			  	I'm guessing that you would have to limit the amount of information that can be gathered about other players outside of special ops.  You would probably have to limit viewing of BRs to only those councils to which you are allied.  Information on power levels, number of fleets, the ranking page in general, would all have to be removed or the information made available only through the use of special ops (making the Agerus more interesting and making expenditures in defense levels more important). Unfortunately, as much as I like the idea of &quot;the fog of war&quot;, I guess that the well coordinated councils (e.g. TE) would share this information outside of game channels and have an advantage over less coordinated councils.  The current open information system actually levels the playing field somewhat since information truly is power.<br />
